      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical R19.2 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented QA procedures. FDA in-house scripts were version-controlled in Git. SQA documentation reviewed and found compliant with required Gradation 2 practices."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from the Ansys verification manual were reproduced with results within 1% of analytical solutions. Custom contact routines were verified against closed-form Hertz contact solutions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed on three systematically refined meshes (coarse, medium, fine). Richardson extrapolation applied; discretization error in peak von Mises stress estimated at 2.3%. GCI < 5% on all quantities of interest."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver residuals converged to 1e-6 for all load steps. Iterative solver tolerance set to 1e-8. Energy balance monitored throughout; no spurious energy accumulation observed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed by a second analyst independent of the primary modeler. Boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions were cross-checked against the ASTM F1717 test protocol. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic material model validated for titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V within the sub-yield loading regime of ASTM F1717 compression-bending. Geometric nonlinearity included via large-displacement formulation. Frictional contact at screw-rod interface modeled with Coulomb friction (mu=0.2) consistent with published tribological data."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from MMPDS-11 for Ti-6Al-4V. Geometric dimensions measured from 11 physical constructs using CMM with ±0.005 mm accuracy. Torque preload on set screws measured and applied as initial conditions. Sensitivity analysis performed on Young's modulus and friction coefficient."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Constructs sourced from the same manufacturing lot as clinical devices. Dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to drawing tolerances."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single environmental condition (ambient, 37°C PBS bath) at a single loading rate (5 mm/min). While this matches the ASTM F1717 protocol, only one test condition was explored, limiting coverage of the loading-rate sensitivity and temperature range relevant to in vivo use. Achieved level therefore falls below required level for this factor."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "FEA input parameters (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions, loading) mapped directly to measured experimental parameters for each of the 11 constructs. Traceability matrix documented linking each model input to its experimental measurement source."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and failure load compared between FEA predictions and experimental measurements using mean error, 95% prediction interval, and U95 uncertainty metric per ASME V&V 40. Mean stiffness prediction error 3.1%; mean failure load prediction error 4.7%. All predictions within experimental uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Quantities of interest (construct stiffness and failure load under compression-bending) are the primary mechanical performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to the regulatory submission claim. QOI selection endorsed by the clinical and regulatory team."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activity replicates the ASTM F1717 compression-bending scenario using production-equivalent hardware. The validation domain — static loading, ambient saline, non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw — is closely aligned with the intended submission scope as described in the claim and requirement documentation, providing high relevance to the regulatory decision context."
    }
  ],
